ted in <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/4.1.0/api/java/org/springframework/boot/security/autoconfigure/web/reactive/ReactiveWebSecurityAutoConfiguration.html\" class=\"apiref\"><code>ReactiveWebSecurityAutoConfiguration</code></a> and <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/4.1.0/api/java/org/\nSpring Security 1181 GTM-W8CQ8TL\"); } else { timer = setTimeout(waitForOnetrustActiveGroups, 250); }}</script>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n    <title>Spring Security :: Spring Boot</title>\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/reference/web/spring-security.html\">\n    <link rel=\"prev\" href=\"graceful-shutdown.html\">\n    <link rel=\"next\" href=\"spring-session.html\">\n    <meta name=\"generator\" content=\"Antora 3.2.0-rc.2\">\n    <script>\n!function (theme, navWidth) {\n  if (theme === 'dark') document.documentElement.classLis\nweb applications 68528 ge\">Spring Security</h1>\n<div id=\"preamble\">\n<div class=\"sectionbody\">\n<div class=\"paragraph\">\n<p>If <a href=\"https://spring.io/projects/spring-security\">Spring Security</a> is on the classpath, then web applications are secured by default.\nThis includes securing Spring Boot&#8217;s <code>/error</code> endpoint.\nSpring Boot relies on Spring Security&#8217;s content-negotiation strategy to determine whether to use <code>httpBasic</code> or <code>formLogin</code>.\nTo add method-level security to a web application, you can also add <a href=\"https://docs.spring.io/spring-security/reference/7.1/api\n\nURL https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/reference/using/build-systems.html\nspring-boot-starter-security 111284 auth2-authorization-server</code></p></td>\n<td class=\"tableblock halign-left valign-top\"><p class=\"tableblock\">Starter for using Spring Authorization Server features (deprecated in favor of <a href=\"#spring-boot-starter-security-oauth2-authorization-server\"><code>sprin