starter-security`. \\n\\nI’m considering adding `spring-boot-test` for context testing with AssertJ, but I should avoid cluttering with unnecessary JUnit asserts. I also have to think about whether to integrate actuator endpoints to ensure meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Actuator and Coverage Needs**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to include the actuator-specific package for meaningful coverage in my Spring application. While normal usage often involves Actuator, I'm wondering if we really need to add only what's necessary for testing. It looks like generated tests can skip over actuator classes, so maybe that extra setup isn't needed for coverage. \\n\\nFor auto-config modules, it seems that starting a Spring app with its auto-config is essential, and I'll need at least a web app for this. I also need to review the dependencies for testing utilities.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating web app security**\\n\\nI'm considering a servlet web app stack with components like the servlet API and Spring Boot autoconfiguration for security. I wonder if adding starter-webmvc introduces unnecessary targets. There’s also a thought about including `spring-boot-actuator`, but I'm noticing the version differences. It's important to check dependencies like `spring-boot-actuator-autoconfigure` for health checks, especially when managing security. But would adding both starter-webmvc and starter-actuator be overkill? I’ll consider the implications carefully to ensure meaningful coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding WebApplicationContextRunner**\\n\\nI’m considering using `WebApplicationContextRunner`, but it might need `spring-web` from `spring-boot-test`. I realize that for a servlet mock environment, `spring-test` should include the mock servlet API, which seems to be missing from the starter-webmvc. My plan is to check if a minimal test compiles and runs with these dependencies. I want to keep things simple without modifying the repo. It’s important to understand Boot 4 packages, so I’ll focus on creating a straightforward Java test.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MAwpdphfrSdtYETNmuuWeL0s|fc_07bbb15f1cf42403016a3eeb7edf6881978b2ef913a8c7c7ff", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; cat > settings.gradle <<'EOF'\npluginManagement { repositories { mavenCentral(); gradlePluginPortal() } }\ndependencyResolutionManagement { repositoriesMode.set(RepositoriesMode.FAIL_ON_PROJECT_REPOS); repositories { mavenCentral() } }\nrootProject.name='probe'\nEOF\ncat > build.gradle <<'EOF'\nplugins { id 'java' }\ndependencies {\n testImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter:5.13.4'\n testImplementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-security:4.1.0'\n testImplementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0'\n testImplementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-webmvc:4.1.0'\n}\ntest { useJUnitPlatform() }\nEOF\nmkdir -p src/test/java/probe; cat > src/test/java/probe/SecurityProbeTest.java <<'EOF'\npackage probe;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.springframework.boot.security.autoconfigure.SecurityAutoConfiguration;\nimport org.springframework.boot.security.autoconfigure.UserDetailsServiceAutoConfiguration;\nimport org.springframework.boot.security.autoconfigure.web.servlet.SecurityFilterAutoConfiguration;\nimport org.springframework.boot.security.autoconfigure.web.servlet.ServletWebSecurityAutoConfiguration;\nimport org.springframework.boot.test.context.runner.WebApplicationContextRunner;\nimport org.springframework.security.web.SecurityFilterChain;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\n\nclass SecurityProbeTest {\n @Test void autoConfiguresServletSecurity() {\n  new WebApplicationContextRunner()\n    .withUserConfiguration(TestController.class)\n    .withConfiguration(org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.AutoConfigurations.of(\n      SecurityAutoConfiguration.class,\n      UserDetailsServiceAutoConfiguration.class,\n      ServletWebSecurityAutoConfiguration.class,\n      SecurityFilterAutoConfiguration.class))\n    .run(context -> assertNotNull(context.getBean(SecurityFilterChain.class)));\n }\n static class TestController {}\n}\nEOF\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/8464-bbee4dc1/gradlew -q test --stacktrace", "timeout": 180}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 689, "output": 1957, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35926, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782508394056, "responseId": "resp_07bbb15f1cf42403016a3eeb6a831881978776905b9ffe8237"}}
