Evaluating JSON deterministic setup**\\n\\nI’m considering how to include compile support for ApplicationContextRunner within a JSON deterministic setup. Adding AssertJ might feel a bit off, especially since the generated agent can handle assertion libraries by itself. The deterministic setup should focus on dependencies that the driver can apply before generation. If we skip AssertJ, does that mean the agent may not use ApplicationContextRunner? Well, I could explore using SpringApplication without the boot-test to simplify things, but I need to consider if I still require all three dependencies: `spring-boot-starter-webmvc`, `spring-boot-test`, and `assertj-core`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nqCd9a4QEm0w5CX2rT3kc1Me|fc_07bbb15f1cf42403016a3eeb8d2f848197811776dcc7b42465", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re\ns=urllib.request.urlopen('https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-dependencies/4.1.0/spring-boot-dependencies-4.1.0.pom').read().decode()\nm=re.search(r'<assertj.version>([^<]+)</assertj.version>',s)\nprint(m.group(1) if m else 'no')\nfor term in ['assertj-core']:\n i=s.find(term); print(i, s[i-100:i+100] if i!=-1 else '')\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5699, "output": 607, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40098, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782508419821, "responseId": "resp_07bbb15f1cf42403016a3eeb84722c8197acd99a2d3e130201"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_nqCd9a4QEm0w5CX2rT3kc1Me|fc_07bbb15f1cf42403016a3eeb8d2f848197811776dcc7b42465", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3.27.7\n-1 \n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782508429910}]}
